dataElements.description:
Select 10 guides at random from period surveyed considered and having the following criteria to be able to analyze the filling and the correct use of the information for decision-making:
- Full-term pregnancy,
- Vertex presentation
- Less than 8 cm of dilation at the first examination,
- Fetal heart rate present at the first examination
- Without obstetric complications at the first examination (multiple births must be considered a complication, and not "normal")
- Be filled by different providers
Analyze the following elements to evaluate the quality of the filling:
- Respect of the time between examinations (FHR every 15 minutes, obstetric exam every hour, Temperature every 2 hours, Uterine contractions every 30 minutes)
- Verification made of the color of the amniotic fluid
- Adequacy of the decision taken when the alert line has been crossed
On the basis of these criteria filled in YES or NO if the labor care guide is filled in systematically and of good quality.

dataElements.description:
Select randomly 10 newborn files and analyze if those elements have been checked during the examination:
- Coloration
- Measurement: weight, height, head circumference, chest circumference
- Constants: temperature, respiratory rate, heart rate, saturation
- Look for signs of respiratory distress
- Reactivity/cry
- Sucking reflex
- Head to toe examination for malformations
